data.title: Dobyns - Bennett High School
data.meta_description: Dobyns - Bennett High School school profile, performance trends and TN state ranking. See how Dobyns - Bennett High School ranks with other Kingsport schools.
data.text:
Summary:

Dobyns - Bennett High School is a public high school located in Kingsport, Tennessee, serving grades 9-12 with a total enrollment of 2,514 students. The school is part of the Kingsport District, which is ranked 29th out of 139 districts in Tennessee and has a 4-star rating from SchoolDigger.

Dobyns - Bennett High School has consistently ranked among the top high schools in Tennessee, with a ranking as high as 11th out of 351 schools in 2015-2016. The school has maintained a 5-star rating from SchoolDigger for several years, indicating excellent overall performance, and outperforms the state and Kingsport District averages in many academic areas, such as proficiency in TNReady/Biology I, TNReady/US History, and TNReady/English II. Additionally, the school has strong performance across different student subgroups, including female students, male students, Asian students, Hispanic students, and special education students, with rankings often in the top quartile or top half of Tennessee high schools.

While Dobyns - Bennett High School generally outperforms nearby schools like Tennessee Online Public School and Science Hill High School, which are also high-performing, the school's performance in some subgroups, such as African American students and students with low socioeconomic status, could be further strengthened to ensure all students are achieving at high levels. Overall, Dobyns - Bennett High School stands out as a consistently high-performing school that excels in many academic areas and supports the success of diverse student groups.
